Package rbvs.product

Class CompositeProduct

  • java.lang.Object
    • rbvs.product.Product
      • rbvs.product.CompositeProduct
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDeepCopy, IProduct, IShoppingCartElement
    public class CompositeProduct
extends Product
    Provides the means to specify a Joint-Product that is a collection of containedProducts. Joint-Products have, besides a name and a discount, a list of Products. A Joint-Product can define a discount that is applied when calculating the total price. The price of the Joint-Product is specified by the list of containedProducts contained in the Joint-Product and the given discount.

    Attributes of the class:

    • discount percentage (as a point number)
    • list of Products

    • Constructor Detail

      • CompositeProduct

        public CompositeProduct​(String name,
                        float discount)
        Constructor that takes two arguments (name and discount) and initializes the product. The price is initialized with zero. If the passed name is NULL the product name will be initialized with an empty string. If the passed discount is below zero the discount is set to zero. In case of a passed discount above 100 the discount is set to 100. If the discount is between zero and 100 percent the Joint-Product is initialized accordingly.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the product
        discount - the discount as a percentage

      • CompositeProduct

        public CompositeProduct​(String name,
                        float discount,
                        ProductCategory category)
        Constructor that takes three arguments (name, discount and category) and initializes the product. The price is initialized with zero.

        If the passed name is NULL the product name will be initialized with an empty string.

        If the passed discount is below zero the discount is set to zero. In case of a passed discount above 100 the discount is set to 100. If the discount is between zero and 100 percent the Joint-Product is initialized accordingly.

        If the passed ProductCategory is NULL, the ProductCategory.DEFAULT value is used.

        Parameters:
        name - the name of the product
        discountPercentage - the discount as a percentage
        category - the category of the product

      • CompositeProduct

        public CompositeProduct​(String name,
                        float discount,
                        Collection<Product> products)
        Constructor that takes three arguments (name, discount and a list of containedProducts) and initializes the product.

        product name: If the passed name is NULL the product name will be initialized with an empty string.

        discount: If the discount is between zero and 100 percent the Joint-Product is initialized accordingly. If the passed discount is below zero percent the discount is set to zero. In case of a discount above 100 percent the discount is initialized with 100 percent.

        containedProducts: If the list of containedProducts is not null, the given containedProducts will be added to the product list of this Joint-Product.

        Parameters:
        name - the name of the product
        discount - the discount
        products - the containedProducts that should be associated with this Joint-Product

        public float getPrice()
        Calculates the total price of the product.

        The price of a CompositeProduct is calculated as the sum of reduced prices of all containedProducts in the product list.
